For location s： \[Y(s)=\beta_0+\beta_1\cdot \text{CTM}(s)\;+\;W(s)\;+\;\varepsilon(s),\\ W(\cdot)\sim \text{GP}\!\big(0,\ \sigma^2\rho_\phi(\cdot)\big),\quad \varepsilon(s)\overset{i.i.d.}{\sim}N(0,\tau^2).\] • \(Y(s)\)：observed PM10 \ • \(\text{CTM}(s)= pm10.ctm\)（协变量）\ • 相关函数 \(\rho_\phi(h)\)：用 指数核 \(\exp(-\phi h)\)

Our goal: Fit the posterior of $ theta=( beta-0,  beta_1,  sigma ^ 2,  tau ^ 2,  phi) $using training points; Perform posterior prediction on ‘unobserved points’ or regular grid $S0 $

Hierarchical modeling: \[ \begin{aligned} \mathbf{Y} \mid \beta,\mathbf{W},\tau^2 &\sim \mathcal{N}(X \beta + \mathbf{W},\ \tau^2 I),\\ \mathbf{W} \mid \sigma^2,\phi &\sim \mathcal{N}(\mathbf{0},\ K),\quad K=\sigma^2 H_{\phi},\ (H_{\phi})_{ij}=e^{-\phi d_{ij}}. \end{aligned} \] Prior： \[ \begin{aligned} & \beta \sim \mathcal N(\mu_\beta, V_\beta)，\text{where} \quad \mu_\beta=\mathbf 0，V_\beta=10^6 I \\ & \sigma^2 \sim \mathrm{IG}(a_\sigma,b_\sigma)，\tau^2 \sim \mathrm{IG}(a_\tau,b_\tau),a_\sigma = 2, \text{where} \quad b_\sigma =1,a_\tau =2,b_\tau =1\\ & \phi \sim \mathrm{Unif}(\phi_{\min},\phi_{\max}) \end{aligned} \]

\[p(\theta\mid y)\propto f(y\mid \theta)\,p(\theta)\]

# 先验 and 初值
D <- fields::rdist(coords_train)
r_max <- max(D); r_min <- quantile(D[D > 0], 0.1)
phi.lo <- 3 / r_max
phi.hi <- 3 / r_min

p <- ncol(X_train)
priors <- list(
  beta.Norm   = list(mu = rep(0, p), cov = diag(1e6, p)),
  sigma.sq.IG = c(2, 1),     
  tau.sq.IG   = c(2, 1),
  phi.Unif    = c(phi.lo, phi.hi)
)
starting <- list(beta = rep(0, p),
                 sigma.sq = var(y_train)/2,
                 tau.sq   = var(y_train)/2,
                 phi      = (phi.lo + phi.hi)/2)
tuning <- list(sigma.sq = 0.1, tau.sq = 0.1, phi = 0.1)

在固定 \(\sigma, \phi, \tau\) 下，\(\beta\) 的条件后验是高斯： \[ \begin{aligned} \Sigma &= \sigma^2 H_\phi + \tau^2 I,\\ V_\beta^{\text{post}} &= \Big(X^\top \Sigma^{-1} X + V_\beta^{-1}\Big)^{-1},\\ m_\beta^{\text{post}} &= V_\beta^{\text{post}}\Big(X^\top \Sigma^{-1} y + V_\beta^{-1}\mu_\beta\Big),\\ \beta\mid y,\theta &\sim \mathcal N\!\big(m_\beta^{\text{post}}, V_\beta^{\text{post}}\big). \end{aligned} \]

sum_post <- function(M) data.frame(
  param = colnames(M),
  mean  = apply(M, 2, mean),
  sd    = apply(M, 2, sd),
  l95   = apply(M, 2, quantile, 0.025),
  u95   = apply(M, 2, quantile, 0.975),
  row.names = NULL
)

post_beta  <- sum_post(Braw)
post_theta <- sum_post(Theta)

posterior_summary <- rbind(
  transform(post_beta,  group = "beta"),
  transform(post_theta, group = "covariance")
)[, c("group","param","mean","sd","l95","u95")]

print(posterior_summary, row.names = FALSE)

Bayesian kriging：\ • goal：\(\displaystyle p(y_0\mid y)=\int p(y_0\mid y,\theta,\beta)\,p(\theta,\beta\mid y)\,d\theta d\beta\).\ • 条件高斯公式对每个样本 \(\theta^{(g)},\beta^{(g)}\)\ \[ \begin{aligned} \mu_0^{(g)} &= X_0\beta^{(g)} + K_0^\top \Sigma^{-1}\big(y - X\beta^{(g)}\big),\\ \Sigma_{0}^{(g)} &= K_{00} - K_0^\top \Sigma^{-1} K_0 + \tau^{2\,(g)} I_m, \end{aligned} \] where \[K=\sigma^{2\,(g)}H_{\phi^{(g)}}，\Sigma=K+\tau^{2\,(g)}I， K_0=\mathrm{cov}(W_0,W)，K_{00}=\mathrm{cov}(W_0,W_0)\]

对每个后验样本 g 从 \(\mathcal N(\mu_0^{(g)},\Sigma_0^{(g)})\)抽一组 \(y_0^{(g)}\)。
